               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-23-person314">
                  JOHN 
                  LOCK
               <interp inst="t18310630-23-person314" type="surname" value="LOCK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-23-person314" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-23-person314" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Policeman. On the 24th of June, I received information and saw the prisoner in Upper Berkeley-street, about a quarter to six o'clock in the evening; on seeing me he ran away - I pursued, overtook him, and took him into custody; I searched him, and found eight silver forks and four silver spoons on him; some were loose in his pockets, and some at the bottom of his trousers - he told me he had received them from another boy, not knowing what they were at the time; he was more than a mile from Mr. Davis - he appeared to be a chimney-sweeper.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-23-person315">
                  ROBERT 
                  PANNELL
               <interp inst="t18310630-23-person315" type="surname" value="PANNELL"></interp>
