             Davis, Esq., who lives in <placeName id="t18310630-23-crimeloc130">Conduit-street, in the parish of St. George, Hanover-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-23-crimeloc130" type="placeName" value="Conduit-street, in the parish of St. George, Hanover-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-23-crimeloc130" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-23-off127 t18310630-23-crimeloc130"></join>. I know this plate to be his - I have not the least doubt of it; it is the exact quantity we lost, and worth between 8l. and 10l. - it was taken from the pantry; the last time I can swear to seeing it safe was the Wednesday before the Friday when it was taken; I missed it on the Saturday - it might have been taken on Thursday; the pantry is down stairs; the area door is occasionally open -I do not know the prisoner.</p>
